airtrafficcontrol.app.menuoptions

Class Option

  • java.lang.Object
    • airtrafficcontrol.app.menuoptions.Option
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AddAFlightOption, AddAListOfFlightsOption, ConfigurationsOption, ConsultFlightDetailsOption, ExitOption, HelpOption_for_EHLsATCAppForConsole, MonitorAirTrafficOption, RemoveAFlightOption, RemoveEmptyAirshipsOption, ReportTransgressionsOption, UpdateDatabaseOption

    public abstract class Option
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class and all its subclasses represent options from an options menu.

    This abstract class serves the purpose of establishing which are the common properties and methods of all options of an OptionsMenu: all options must have a final field title and a final field description , both accessible for reading, and must have an execute and an executeToConsole methods.

    Implementation notes

    • When a class extends Option, its main feature should be the implementation of the method execute. Due to that, it is strongly recommended that all instances of a subclass of Option store the same string in the field title (a title that shortly says the objective of this method) and that all instances store the same string in the field description (a short description of the actions performed by this method and some usage tips about the input-output interaction). One way of doing that is to create only one constructor method, without arguments, that initializes these fields.
    • Since the fields title and description must be final fields, their visibility was chosen to be public.
    Author:
    Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade
